      "message": "[warning] Line 70: This unconditionally runs `$(YFFI_RUSTUP) target add` for cross builds, but `YFFI_RUSTUP` is empty when a system `cargo` exists without `rustup`. That makes the rule execute `target add ...` and fail on hosts that package Rust without rustup. Gate this command on rustup being available, or make the no-system-cargo/bootstrap case the only one that requires rustup. For example:\n```suggestion\nifneq ($(YFFI_CARGO_TARGET_ARG),)\nifneq ($(YFFI_RUSTUP),)\n\t$(YFFI_RUST_ENV) $(YFFI_RUSTUP) target add $(YFFI_RUST_TARGET)\nendif\nendif\n```",
